== Honey Walnut Crostini ==

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Slice @Demi-Baguette{1} crosswise into 8 rounds (16 rounds for 4); spread out on
a #baking sheet{} and drizzle with @Olive Oil{2%tablespoon}. Toast on top rack
until golden brown, ~{5-10%minutes}. (For 4, if necessary, divide rounds
between two baking sheets; toast on top and middle racks.) (Reserve baking
sheet for Step 5.)

Place @Ricotta Cheese{4%ounce} in a #small bowl{}; whisk in a large drizzle of
olive oil. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Spread ricotta on toasted baguette rounds; drizzle with @Honey{4%teaspoon} and
sprinkle with @Walnuts{1/2%ounce}.

> TIP: Prefer to serve the crostini with the main course? Toast now and assemble
> right before serving!

== Garlic Mashed Potatoes ==

Dice @Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}.
Trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Strip @Rosemary{1/4%ounce}
leaves from stems; mince leaves until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4 servings). Halve,
peel, and mince @Shallot{1} until you have 2 TBSP (3 TBSP for 4).

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain.

Melt @Butter{3%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4 servings) in empty pot used for potatoes
over medium heat. Add garlic; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add drained potatoes and @Sour Cream{1.5%tablespoon}; mash with a #potato masher{}
until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed.
Season with salt and pepper. Top with @Parmesan Cheese{3%tablespoon}.

== Crispy Panko ==

While potatoes cook, heat a drizzle of olive oil in a medium, preferably
nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup};
season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, until golden brown,
~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

== Caramelized Brussels Sprouts ==

Toss Brussels sprouts on #sheet{} used for crostini with a large drizzle of
olive oil, salt, and pepper. Roast on top rack until browned and crispy,
~{15-20%minutes}.

Carefully transfer to bowl with toasted panko; toss to combine. Season with half
the minced rosemary, salt, and pepper.

== Balsamic & Fig Beef Tenderloin ==

While Brussels sprouts roast, pat @Beef Tenderloin Filets{10%ounce} dry with
#paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in pan used for panko over
medium-high heat. Add beef and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.
Wipe out pan.

Melt 1 TBSP butter in same pan over medium heat. Add minced shallot; cook until
fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @Beef Stock Concentrate{1}, @Fig Jam{1}, @Balsamic Vinegar{5%teaspoon},
2 TBSP water (4 TBSP for 4 servings), any resting juices from beef, and remaining
minced rosemary to taste. Cook until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season
with salt and pepper.

Divide mashed potatoes, Brussels sprouts, and beef between plates. Top beef
with sauce and serve.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.